This paper deals with deep learning techniques for semantic understanding of urban scenes in autonomous driving systems. The paper proposes a novel unsupervised domain adaptation strategy that involves adversarial learning and self-teaching techniques. The paper focuses on semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task, hence it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category. The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The paper deals with autonomous driving systems, which is a robotics application, hence it is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) category. Finally, the paper involves techniques for improving the performance of deep learning models, which makes it likely to belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category.
